    <note type="biography">
        <p>Botanist, clergyman, and antiquary. Schoolfellow of CD’s in Shrewsbury, 1817. Priest at Lichfield, 1843–6. Curate of St Giles’s, Shrewsbury, 1846–8. Edited the <hi rend="italic">Transactions of the Shropshire Archaeological Society</hi> for many years. Published <hi rend="italic">The flora of Shropshire</hi> (1841).</p></note>
